725991f-a.title: Queens: 175th Street - Douglas Avenue
725991f-a.text:
175th Street, east side, at the head of Douglas Avenue,
showing old Jamaica homes, just south of the Long Island
Railroad.
P. L. Sperr  April 1, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS

727235f-a.title: Queens: Liberty Avenue - 175th Street
727235f-a.text:
Liberty Avenue, north side, at 175th Street. Several very
old houses can be seen on both sides of 175th Street, formerly
known as Larch Street. In 1891 the property was owned by J. Day.
This part of Liberty Avenue was formerly South Street, one of the
aain east-eest highways in this part of the county.
P. L. Sperr  April 1, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS
